rootNodes.name: Trading Bot Layers
rootNodes.config:
{
    "title": "Trading Bot Layers",
    "summary": "Hi! I'm going to show you everything about the layers of the trading bot... the ones featured on charts associated with trading sessions!",
    "subTitle": "",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "trading-bot",
    "definition": "Let's get on with it! The ->Trading Bot-> outputs dozens of products, and they're all featured in three separate layer managers:",
    "bulletArray": [
        [
            "Trading Engine",
            " features layers that turn on and off the reporting of values of nodes in the ->Trading Engine-> hierarchy."
        ],
        [
            "Trading System",
            " features layers that turn on and off multiple types of reports at the level of the ->Trading System->."
        ],
        [
            "Simulation Objects",
            " features layers that turn on and off the rendering of visual information over the charts."
        ]
    ],
    "paragraph1": "",
    "callOut": "",
    "paragraph2": "",
    "note": "",
    "tip": "",
    "important": "",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "",
    "slider": "toTop",
    "documentationURL": ""
}

tutorialSteps.name: Load a Fresh Workspace
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Load a Fresh Workspace!", "gif": "", "image": "workspace", "definition": "But before we go any further, let's make sure we are starting with a fresh workspace!", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "", "paragraph2": "", "note": "Workspaces with the prefix Plugin \u2192 comes with the software. The rest are yours. When you open a plugin workspace a copy of it is made for you. Plugins allways remain unchanged.", "tip": "", "important": "This tutorial requires starting with a fresh Plugin \u2192 Weak-hands Buster v2 workspace. So, unless you loaded the plugin workspace right before starting, please select it from the workspace panel on the right and come back to me after the workspace loads—just click Resume on my menu!", "warning": "", "position": "", "slider": "toTop", "documentationURL": "", "positionAtReferenceParent": true, "workspaces": "Open" }

tutorialSteps.name: Freeze! Don't Move!
tutorialSteps.config:
{
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "subTitle": "Feeze! Don't Move!",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "stop-loss",
    "definition": "I've got something to tell you before we move on, but I'm struggling to find the right words... I just wouldn't want to come across as a control freak!",
    "paragraph1": "It's not like you may break something or anything... nothing to fear at all... it's just that... I relay on the fresh state of the workspace to predict what you see when I take you to places and show you stuff. I may comment on what you will experience along the journey, and use my predictions to make the tour juicier and interesting! So...",
    "callOut": "Don't fool around too much unless I tell you to! I mean, you may look around, but don't make a mess! Fine! Do what you want! If you ever feel I lost you, just start over with a fresh workspace!",
    "paragraph2": "",
    "note": "",
    "tip": "",
    "important": "",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "",
    "slider": "toTop",
    "documentationURL": "",
    "workspaces": "Close"
}

tutorialSteps.name: Let's Mine Some Data!
tutorialSteps.config: { "subTitle": "Let's Mine Some Data!", "gif": "", "image": "run", "definition": "We'll do some ->Data Mining-> so that we may then run a quick ->Backtesting Session->! We'll explore these layers on the resulting simulation...", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "Select Run All Exchange Data Tasks on the data mining node menu!", "paragraph2": "", "note": "", "tip": "The sensor bot will run from January 1st, 2020, along with the indicators required by the Weak-hands Buster ->Trading System->.", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Left", "slider": "toTop", "pressButton": "", "positionAtReferenceParent": true, "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: Are We Up to Date?
tutorialSteps.config: { "subTitle": "Are We Up to Date?", "gif": "", "image": "indicator-process-instance", "definition": "Now we have to wait a bit! When all processes reach the 100% mark, we may proceed!", "paragraph1": "As you probably know, the time required to mine data depends on many things. If you already have some of this data from previous activities, it may be faster!", "callOut": "Monitor the processes for all indicators in the Sparta and Masters data mines. When all of them reach 100%, then stop the data mining operation and click Next to continue.", "paragraph2": "", "tip": "Bollinger Channels will likely be last!", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Left", "slider": "toTop", "documentationURL": "", "positionAtReferenceParent": true }

tutorialSteps.name: Ready. Set. Go!
tutorialSteps.config: { "subTitle": "Ready. Set. Go!", "gif": "", "image": "task", "definition": "Let's do some backtesting! This should be rather quick, as we are testing six months' worth of historic data only. Remember to stop the ->Data Mining-> first!", "paragraph1": "Running a trading task is quite similar to running a data mining task. The difference lies in that—after running the task—you also need to run the trading session.", "callOut": "Select Run on the ->Task-> menu and then select Run on the ->Backtesting Session-> menu.", "paragraph2": "", "note": "When the progress notice get's to the 100% mark and stops (sometimes only 99%), then stop the task and click Next to continue.", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Left", "slider": "toTop", "positionAtReferenceParent": true, "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialTopics.name: Trading Engine Layers
tutorialTopics.config:
{
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "subTitle": "Trading Engine Layers",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "trading-engine",
    "definition": "You are familiar with the concept of the ->Trading Engine->, right? I will teach you wich layers affect which sections of the hierarchy so that you may access the info at will!",
    "paragraph1": "I'm assuming you've done the Welcome tutorial... Remember when you split the screen in half? You slid the mouse pointer over the candles on the chart, and for each candle, you could see the value of certain nodes in the trading engine hierarchy, right?",
    "callOut": "Well, that's what it's all about! When you turn a certain layer on, you turn on the visualization of values for a certain section of the hierarchy.",
    "paragraph2": "Let's take a closer look!",
    "note": "",
    "tip": "",
    "important": "",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "Right",
    "slider": "toBottom",
    "documentationURL": ""
}

tutorialSteps.name: 1, 2, 3, Counting!
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "1, 2, 3, Counting!", "gif": "", "image": "episode-counters", "definition": "Let's test the first ->Layer-> in the Trading Engine ->Layer Manager->: ->Episode Counters->.", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "Turn the layer on and slide your mouse pointer over the chart, from the far left to the far right-hand side of your screen!", "paragraph2": "", "note": "", "tip": "See what happens with the various counters on the hierarchy below... that is, ->Periods->, ->Strategies->, ->Positions->, and so on! You should see something similar to what I show in the video on the next step...", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toMiddle", "documentationURL": "", "positionAtReferenceParent": true }

tutorialSteps.name: GIF
How About the Rest?
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "How About the Rest?", "gif": "", "image": "episode", "definition": "Now, why don't the nodes further to the left show their values too? Say, ->Exit Type->, ->Status->, ->End Rate->, ->Begin Rate->, and so on?", "paragraph1": "Let's change that!", "callOut": "Scroll the Trading Engine layer manager until you find the Current Episode layer. Turn it on!", "paragraph2": "Now slide your mouse pointer again... et voil!", "note": "", "tip": "By turning layers on and off, you turn on and off system's ability to report the values on different sections of the ->Trading Engine-> hierarchy!", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toMiddle", "documentationURL": "", "positionAtReferenceParent": true }

tutorialSteps.name: Et Voil
tutorialSteps.config:
{ "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Et Voil!", "gif": "", "image": "current", "definition": "So, we turned on the Episode Counters and the Current Episode layers... let's take a look at the hierarchy...", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "Track your way up the hierarchy to discover what exactly we were looking at all this time...", "paragraph2": "Right! In the beginning ->Periods->, ->Strategies->, and ->Positions-> where showing their values because they are under the ->Episode Counters-> node of the hierachy... the one we turned on first!

If you follow the hierarchy upstream, you will find the ->Episode-> node, and if you keep going further upstream, you'll find the ->Current-> node. Exactly! Current Episode!.", "note": "", "tip": "", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toTop", "documentationURL": "", "positionAtReferenceParent": true }

tutorialSteps.name: Compartmentalize It!
tutorialSteps.config:
{
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "subTitle": "Compartmentalize It!",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "bot-layers",
    "definition": "The reason why the access to values in the hierarchy is compartmentalized in layers is that layers correspond to data products output by the bot.",
    "paragraph1": "Compartmentalization of definitions—and information in general—is a theme in and of itself throughout the system, as it is one of the mechanisms by which complexity is successfully administered.",
    "callOut": "When you need to use this feature to track values on the trading engine hierarchy, you may choose to turn on multiple layers at once... even all of them if you wish! Just keep in mind that the more layers you turn on, the more files de UI reads, thus the more load you put on your hardware!",
    "paragraph2": "",
    "note": "",
    "tip": "",
    "important": "",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "Right",
    "slider": "toTop",
    "documentationURL": ""
}

tutorialSteps.name: The Elefant in the Room
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Elefant? What Elefant?", "gif": "", "image": "strategy", "definition": "Will someone please acknowledge the elefant in the room? Why did those counters point to one or two strategies and one position?", "paragraph1": "It's time to look into the Simulation Objects layer manager...", "callOut": "Go to the Simulation Objects layer manager and turn on the ->Strategies-> layer.", "paragraph2": "What's that? It's a strategy! We are in a simulation! The Strategies layer marks the span of time on which a strategy is active. Notice the ->Plotter Panel-> that drifted to the corner when you turned the layer on. Now, point your mouse to the span of time between the strategy brakets and see what happens... ", "note": "", "tip": "", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toBottom", "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: Making Sense of Objects
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Making Sense of Objects", "gif": "", "image": "layer", "definition": "The layers in the Simulation Objects layer manager feature visual representations of the data that makes up simulations.", "paragraph1": "In other words, each of these layers render graphics over the charts that help us visualize—therefore, better understand—what happens during a trading session.", "callOut": "", "paragraph2": "", "note": "Each layer may feature plotter panels which usually display the hard data associated with the concept represented by the particular layer.", "tip": "Notice how the data in the panel becomes visible only when the pointer of the mouse lies within the candles engulfed by the object.", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Center", "slider": "toBottom", "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: What About the Position?
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "What About the Position?", "gif": "", "image": "position", "definition": "As you very clearly pointed, the episode counters showed a strategy, but also a position... what about that?", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "Scroll down the Simulation Objects layer manager and turn on the ->Position Base Asset-> layer!", "paragraph2": "Nice! A green triangle means that the position was a hit! It would be red otherwise!", "note": "The horizontal side of the triangle marks the ->Entry Target Rate->. The vertical side marks the datetime the position was closed. The vertex away from the horizontal side is the ->Exit Target Rate->.", "tip": "", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Center", "slider": "toBottom", "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: The Beauty of the Triangle
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "The Beauty of the Triangle", "gif": "", "image": "bullet-warning", "definition": "I'm sure you would agree that the triangle is a quick visual clue to grasp how the trade went in a glimpse!", "paragraph1": "That's one of the core ideas behind these visualization features: quick and effective communication. ", "callOut": "", "paragraph2": "", "note": "The second core idea is that—by being able to see what went on with the session—it is easier to spot the weaknesses in your strategies, and how you may be able to improve them!", "tip": "On a side note, notice that the data displayed on panels is the same data available on the ->Trading Engine-> hierarchy.", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toBottom", "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: Why 3 Position Layers?
tutorialSteps.config:
{
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "subTitle": "Why 3 Position Layers?",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "position",
    "definition": "Did you notice there are three different layers about positions? ->Position->, ->Position Base Asset->, and ->Position Quoted Asset->!",
    "paragraph1": "I'll give you the short version: ",
    "callOut": "The system keeps the accounts relative to both the base asset and the quoted asset. It also keeps a consolidated account of both assets (hence, position). What set of accounts is relevant to you depends on how the strategy is designed!",
    "paragraph2": "",
    "note": "",
    "tip": "",
    "important": "Reading this documentation page is a must to fully understand this concept.",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "Left",
    "slider": "toBottom",
    "documentationURL": "https://docs.superalgos.org/suite-trading-engine-base-asset-and-quoted-asset.html"
}

tutorialSteps.name: Phased Management
tutorialSteps.config:
{
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "subTitle": "Phased Management",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "phase",
    "definition": "The ->Manage Stage-> enables the management of your stop loss and take profit targets in phases. Let's see how that looks in simulations...",
    "paragraph1": "",
    "callOut": "Find the Stop Loss and the Take Profit layers and turn them on!",
    "paragraph2": "It's probably self-explanatory, right? The ->Phase-> icon marks the switching of phases, thus, of the ->Formula-> used to determine each target.",
    "note": "",
    "tip": "This is a fantastic feature when designing strategies, as you can literally see what the formula does, and how phases change!",
    "important": "",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "Right",
    "slider": "toBottom",
    "documentationURL": ""
}

tutorialSteps.name: Orders in Order
tutorialSteps.config:
{
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "subTitle": "Orders in Order",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "bullet-market-sell-order",
    "definition": "You're familiar with the visualization of limit orders from the Welcome tutorial. It's time for market orders to shine!",
    "paragraph1": "Weak-hands Buster V.2—born with earlier versions of the system—uses single market orders to get in and out of positions. Let's see how those look over the charts...",
    "callOut": "Find the Market Buy Orders and Market Sell Orders layers and turn them on!",
    "paragraph2": "",
    "note": "Like with limit orders, a red bullet means a sell order, and a green bullet means a buy order. ",
    "tip": "",
    "important": "",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "Right",
    "slider": "toBottom",
    "documentationURL": ""
}

tutorialSteps.name: Stages & Time
tutorialSteps.config:
{
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "subTitle": "Stages & Time",
    "gif": "",
    "image": "close-stage-event",
    "definition": "Layers corresponding to stages, that is, ->Trigger Stage->, ->Open Stage->, ->Close Stage->, and ->Manage Stage-> are markers of spans of time.",
    "paragraph1": "That is, they signal the span of time on which each stage was open.",
    "callOut": "Try them out! Find the layers of the different stages and turn them on!",
    "paragraph2": "",
    "note": "",
    "tip": "Feel free to turn off a few of the layers you have on at the moment, for clarity!",
    "important": "",
    "warning": "",
    "position": "Right",
    "slider": "toBottom",
    "documentationURL": ""
}

tutorialSteps.name: Episode X
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Episode X", "gif": "", "image": "episode", "definition": "There's one layer left... ->Episode->!. It marks the duration of the episode and features several plotter panels...", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "Turn the Episode layer on!", "paragraph2": "In this case, the episode is six months long, so all you will see is a line at the bottom of the screen, and the episode icon on both sides, signaling the episode is longer than the period represented on screen.", "note": "As usual, the plotter panels feature information that explained on the ->Trading Engine-> section of the documentation.", "tip": "", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toBottom", "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialTopics.name: Trading System Layers
tutorialTopics.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Trading System Layers", "gif": "", "image": "trading-system", "definition": "The last layer manager is about the ->Trading System-> that features the trading rules for the simulation!", "paragraph1": "These layers work similar to those in the Trading Engine layer manager: they show information on the design space, not on the charts. The differenceis that these show stuff on the trading system hierarchy!", "callOut": "", "paragraph2": "", "note": "These layers are particularly useful when designing, testing, and debugging strategies! Just wait and see!", "tip": "Before continuing, turn some Simulation Objects layers off to avoid cluttering up the screen!", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toBottom", "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: Trading System Errors!
tutorialSteps.config:
{ "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Trading System Errors!", "gif": "", "image": "bullet-error", "definition": "When writing conditions and formulas, you may make mistakes. Remember conditions must evaluate to true or false and formulas to a number? ", "paragraph1": "Well, if they don't, you will get an error! Turning on this layer when you're going back and forth crafting and testing a strategy is a must!", "callOut": "There are no errors in this trading system, but I just planted a fake one so that you may see how they are reported! Look at the ->Formula-> on the left!", "paragraph2": "Now, what if the section of the hierarchy was collapsed? Would you still be able to see error messages?
Let's run a quick test! Collapse the ->Initial Targets-> node!", "note": "", "tip": "", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toMiddle", "setErrorMessageReferenceParent": "This is formula has a fake error!", "positionAtReferenceParent": true, "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: Trading System Highlights
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Trading System Highlights!", "gif": "", "image": "bullet-info", "definition": "Whenever something relevant happens with any given node in the trading system hierarchy, the node is highlighted!", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "Turn the Trading System Highlights layer on, slide your mouse over the chart, and check these conditions and situations! Now place the mouse pointer over the candle where the strategy is triggered... (08 Mar 2020 at 01 hs)...", "paragraph2": "", "note": "Conditions are highlighted when they validate true; situations, when all conditions validate true; stages and phases, when they become active, and so on!", "tip": "", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toMiddle", "positionAtReferenceParent": true, "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: GIF
Trading System Values!
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Trading System Values!", "gif": "", "image": "formula", "definition": "The Trading System Values layers works like the layers on the Trading Engine layer manager showing the values of nodes...", "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "Turn the Trading System Values layer on, slide your mouse over the chart and check the stop formulas!", "paragraph2": "", "note": "The common theme among these layers is that they provide on-the-fly information about each node, for each candle!", "tip": "Is it fair to say that our ->Trading Bot-> is 100% acccountable?", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toMiddle", "positionAtReferenceParent": true, "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: The Rest of the Crew
tutorialSteps.config: { "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "The Rest of the Crew!", "gif": "", "image": "bot-layers", "definition": "The rest of the layers are virtually self-explanatory once you understand the standard workings... so, I'll be brief!", "bulletArray": [ [ "Status,", "for nodes which have one! " ], [ "Progress,", "for nodes that may feature an indication of progress!" ], [ "Running,", "for nodes that are evaluated at certain points in time!" ], [ "Announcements,", "for announcements set up at the trading system, currently broadcasted over Telegram!" ], [ "Warnings,", "when something unusual happens but is not considered an error!" ], [ "System Info,", "may be displayed on many nodes, sort of like a verbose mode. " ] ], "paragraph1": "", "callOut": "", "paragraph2": "", "note": "", "tip": "", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "Right", "slider": "toMiddle", "documentationURL": "" }

tutorialSteps.name: Time To Go Out and Play!
tutorialSteps.config:
{ "title": "", "summary": "", "subTitle": "Time To Go Out and Play!", "gif": "", "image": "play", "definition": "That's all folks! We've covered it all! Now it's time to go out and play! Have fun!", "paragraph1": "Take some time to explore these layers, paying special attention to those you feel will be of the most use.", "callOut": "Remember, the Trading Bot Layers are a fundamental tool when designing, testing, and debugging strategies!

See you next time!", "paragraph2": "", "note": "", "tip": "Drop by the documentation for more info!", "important": "", "warning": "", "position": "", "slider": "toMiddle", "documentationURL": "" }
